audio:
🎤 **If your bot cannot play music:**
- Check if it is muted/server muted
- Try changing voice region
- Check that the issue is being caused by the bot, not you or the server
- Check for errors in the console
- Try `!restart` to restart the bot or `!disconnect` and then `!summon` to reconnect the bot.
- Try moving the bot to a new voice channel and then back, or using `!disconnect`, `!summon`, and then `!play your music`. 
 **This is a discord issue and we can't do anything about it.**

🎤 **If your bot is lagging when playing music:**
- Check CPU/disk usage
- Can your PC/the VPS' bandwidth/speed handle the bot?
- Is there an issue on https://status.discordapp.com/

file extension:
🚧 A file extension, sometimes called a *file suffix* or a *filename extension*, is the character or group of characters after the period that make up an entire file name.

The file extension helps an operating system, like Windows, determine which program on your computer the file is associated with.

For example, the file **myhomework.docx** ends in *docx*, a file extension that might be associated with Microsoft Word on your computer. When you attempt to open this file, Windows sees that the file ends in a DOCX extension, which it already knows should be opened with the Microsoft Word program.

File extensions also often indicate the *file type*, or *file format*, of the file... but not always. Any file's extensions can be renamed but that won't convert the file to another format or change anything about the file other than this portion of its name.

Reference: http://pcsupport.about.com/od/termsf/g/file_extension.htm

options.ini.ini:
⚠ Check for **options.ini.ini**
If you get a problem with "OwnerID not specified" etc, check that your config file is saved as `options.ini`.
By default, Windows hides file extensions, so you should check you **haven't** named this file `options.ini.ini`.
This is a common problem. If you have an `options` and `options.ini` file in your config folder, the correct one is `options`.
parsing: ⚠ If your traceback says **Source contains parsing errors**, it is because the file you have edited is incorrectly format. The exact line that the issue is on will be shown underneath, allowing you to check it and resolve the issue. If you still can't figure out what your issue is, let us know.
path:
⚠ **I can't clone using Git - the destination already exists**
This is because in the location you're running the Git command (shown to the left of the command), you already have a folder with the name you typed (by default, `MusicBot`).

Delete this folder to be able to continue with cloning. If you've previously used the bot, you should backup your `options.ini`, `permissions.ini` and `autoplaylist.txt`. **If you are updating the bot, you don't need to clone again**, just type `!tag latest` here for information.
pip:
📥 Updating **pip**
**Windows**: `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`
**Linux/Mac**: `python3.5 -m pip install --upgrade pip`

On **Windows**, if Python doesn't install itself on your PATH right, you may get an **error**. Try either of these commands in this case:
`py -3 -m pip install --upgrade pip`
`C:\\Windows\\py.exe -3.5 -m pip install --upgrade pip`"

vps:
**What's a VPS you say?!**
A virtual private server (VPS) is a virtual machine sold as a service by an Internet hosting service. A VPS runs its own copy of an operating system, and customers have superuser-level access to that operating system instance, so they can install almost any software that runs on that OS. This means that you can run the MusicBot 24/7 and allow yourself to turn off your computer or let it sleep every so often.

Recommended VPS hosts:
**AWS:** https://aws.amazon.com/free/ While AWS has a free tier, it is only limited data usage under this plan. You may still pay montly for it, and you don't get a any customer support if an issue should arise.

**Digital Ocean:** https://m.do.co/c/04df8e10578f You can run the MusicBot easily under the $5 per month plan. This is a set monthly payment and can use more data than AWS allows, you will also get customer support at no additional cost. *Also if you use the URL in this post you can get a $10 credit to your account when you sign up.*
